results.name: Rearrangement of Fibonacci numbers such that sum of two consecutive terms is a prime.
comment: a(11) = F(67671), the 67671st Fibonacci number. This has over 14000 decimal digits and is too large to display here. - _Ryan Propper_, Jun 16 2006
mathematica: l = {1, 1}; Do[k = 1; While[MemberQ[l, Fibonacci[k]] || !PrimeQ[Last[l] + Fibonacci[k]], k++ ]; AppendTo[l, Fibonacci[k]]; Print[l], {n, 9}] (* _Ryan Propper_, Jun 16 2006 *)
